00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:02,170 --> 00:00:03,870
Chiaki Hosho?

2
00:00:03,870 --> 00:00:07,540
Would it be okay
if I borrowed Ms. Minase for a bit?

3
00:00:07,540 --> 00:00:11,570
I'd like to ask her to be the replacement
for an actress who bailed.

4
00:00:11,570 --> 00:00:15,820
I've always loved you.

5
00:00:15,820 --> 00:00:17,820
A movie starring Mr. Hosho?

6
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:21,180
Apparently, Mr. Hosho recommended you
after seeing your acting.

7
00:00:21,180 --> 00:00:23,230
No matter how close you get to him,

8
00:00:23,230 --> 00:00:25,980
don't make any mistakes
with Mr. Hosho, alright?

9
00:00:25,980 --> 00:00:28,120
God, she's such an eyesore.

10
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:30,560
I wish she'd just disappear from my sight.

11
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:32,790
You seem pretty happy too, Chiaki.

12
00:00:32,790 --> 00:00:35,370
Did you find your true love?

13
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:38,940
The girl I'm working on
is harder to reel in than usual.

14
00:00:38,940 --> 00:00:40,700
Oh, hey, let's make a bet.

15
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:42,920
If you can't get her in three months,

16
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:44,580
give me that watch.

17
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:47,050
Can't you stop doing that already?

18
00:00:47,050 --> 00:00:49,790
When you finally find
someone you actually love,

19
00:00:49,790 --> 00:00:51,350
it'll only cause you trouble.

20
00:00:51,350 --> 00:00:54,790
I love seeing
how girls from a happy household look

21
00:00:54,790 --> 00:01:00,160
when they make that look of despair.

22
00:01:01,340 --> 00:01:03,570
Ready? Action!

23
00:01:14,710 --> 00:01:15,867
- Cut!
- Cut!

24
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:17,760
- Okay!
- Okay!

25
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,160
- Thanks for your hard work.
- Thank you.

26
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:25,447
I'll head out first.

27
00:01:25,447 --> 00:01:27,347
Thanks for your hard work.

28
00:01:29,910 --> 00:01:31,560
Oh no.

29
00:01:33,070 --> 00:01:36,950
<i>Today's the dance lesson for the new song.</i>

30
00:01:36,950 --> 00:01:39,150
<i>I have to go if I can, even a little bit,</i>

31
00:01:39,150 --> 00:01:42,190
<i>so I don't cause trouble for everyone.</i>

32
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,700
Are they on break?

33
00:02:42,159 --> 00:02:45,690
<i>Your performance today was really good.</i>

34
00:02:45,690 --> 00:02:48,090
<i>Do your best with your dance practice.</i>

35
00:02:48,090 --> 00:02:50,660
The salon you recommended
was amazing, Rina.

36
00:02:50,660 --> 00:02:52,780
- Right?
- Good work today. Sorry for...

37
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:55,170
Really? It's super pretty, isn't it?

38
00:02:55,170 --> 00:02:56,730
Hey there...

39
00:03:06,410 --> 00:03:09,730
What do I do? It's gone!

40
00:03:09,730 --> 00:03:11,570
Huh? What's wrong?

41
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,330
Anna, what's wrong?

42
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:21,200
The necklace is gone.

43
00:03:22,090 --> 00:03:23,520
The one you're always wearing?

44
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:28,350
Yeah, the one with the diamond in the heart.

45
00:03:30,310 --> 00:03:31,640
It's so precious to me.

46
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:34,210
My dad gave it to me.

47
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:36,680
Did you drop it somewhere?

48
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:39,510
No, I always keep it in my bag.

49
00:03:40,490 --> 00:03:42,080
And...

50
00:03:43,410 --> 00:03:46,360
I had it before we went on break.

51
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:55,320
Hey, you were in here alone earlier, right?

52
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:58,970
Could be her.

53
00:03:58,970 --> 00:04:01,310
I mean, she's broke.

54
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:03,060
Wait, please...

55
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:04,890
Are you accusing me of stealing it?

56
00:04:04,890 --> 00:04:07,410
I kept my mouth shut all this time...

57
00:04:09,390 --> 00:04:15,330
but this isn't the first time
that I've lost something.

58
00:04:15,330 --> 00:04:16,630
Huh?

59
00:04:16,630 --> 00:04:20,160
I thought it'd hurt our group dynamics,

60
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:22,350
so I kept quiet until now.

61
00:04:25,970 --> 00:04:30,820
Hey, Ama, please, don't hide it!

62
00:04:30,820 --> 00:04:34,050
If you tell me honestly, I'll forgive you.

63
00:04:34,050 --> 00:04:35,370
You're mistaken.

64
00:04:35,370 --> 00:04:38,300
If you doubt me, then look in my bag.

65
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:40,290
What's going on?

66
00:04:40,290 --> 00:04:43,890
Mr. Suzui! Listen to this.

67
00:04:43,890 --> 00:04:47,990
The truth is, Anna's necklace went missing.

68
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:11,040
Cut, cut!

69
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:12,970
- Cut!
- Ms. Minase, your position!

70
00:05:12,970 --> 00:05:15,910
- Huh?
- Get closer to Hachimura.

71
00:05:17,110 --> 00:05:19,590
Ama, a little more this way. Over here.

72
00:05:19,590 --> 00:05:21,210
Thank you very much.

73
00:05:21,210 --> 00:05:23,770
Focus, focus!

74
00:05:23,770 --> 00:05:26,160
- I'm sorry!
- Let's do one more time.

75
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,220
I'm sorry.

76
00:05:27,220 --> 00:05:29,840
Oh, don't worry. It's fine.

77
00:05:32,170 --> 00:05:33,740
Really, don't worry about it.

78
00:05:33,740 --> 00:05:36,260
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay, it's okay.

79
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:45,510
There you are.

80
00:05:45,510 --> 00:05:47,270
Chiaki.

81
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:52,490
Huh?

82
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:55,560
You seem down.

83
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:58,160
No, I'm fine.

84
00:05:59,010 --> 00:06:01,330
Something's definitely wrong.

85
00:06:04,590 --> 00:06:07,040
If you want, I'll listen.

86
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,880
Really, it's nothing.

87
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:18,800
I want to help you, Ama.

88
00:06:22,410 --> 00:06:24,810
You should rely on me more.

89
00:06:33,670 --> 00:06:36,330
Actually, lately,

90
00:06:36,330 --> 00:06:39,170
I'm not getting along with my group.

91
00:06:40,990 --> 00:06:45,150
I see... So that's what happened...

92
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,480
That must have been hard.

93
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:55,140
I can tell you wouldn't do that,

94
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:57,920
even though we haven't
known each other for long.

95
00:07:02,740 --> 00:07:04,340
It's okay.

96
00:07:08,140 --> 00:07:10,140
I'm on your side.

97
00:07:12,330 --> 00:07:14,670
Chiaki.

98
00:07:14,670 --> 00:07:16,290
Oh, right.

99
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:20,490
Let's go get a meal together sometime,
just the two of us.

100
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:23,130
Huh?

101
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:29,190
You've just started acting,
so I'm sure it's tough.

102
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:33,540
You need a break once in a while.

103
00:07:34,810 --> 00:07:37,130
Thank you.

104
00:07:39,410 --> 00:07:40,910
But...

105
00:07:40,910 --> 00:07:44,460
I feel like I shouldn't rely on you
any more than this.

106
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:46,220
Huh?

107
00:07:46,220 --> 00:07:49,830
Just having you listen to me like this

108
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:53,050
has already made me feel so much lighter.

109
00:07:53,050 --> 00:07:55,350
To have a senior like you, Chiaki...

110
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:58,190
I'm really lucky.

111
00:08:01,530 --> 00:08:03,530
Ms. Minase, you're up.

112
00:08:03,530 --> 00:08:04,830
Okay.

113
00:08:05,730 --> 00:08:07,410
Thank you very much.

114
00:08:07,410 --> 00:08:09,200
Excuse me.

115
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,300
Good work.

116
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,350
Hey, Chiaki.

117
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:35,960
Yeah?

118
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:39,230
Your mom was outside earlier.

119
00:08:42,510 --> 00:08:46,120
When I said you weren't here, she left.

120
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:51,370
Yeah.

121
00:08:51,370 --> 00:08:52,870
Thanks.

122
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:56,172
[Mom]

123
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:17,770
Okay, let's take a break.

124
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,810
Anna, let's go get some food.

125
00:09:25,810 --> 00:09:27,310
Yeah, let's go.

126
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:28,800
Oh.

127
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,540
Don't forget to bring your bag.

128
00:09:32,930 --> 00:09:34,330
Let's go.

129
00:09:37,530 --> 00:09:38,890
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

130
00:09:38,890 --> 00:09:40,080
I'm hungry.

131
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,730
Hey, what do you want to eat?

132
00:09:41,730 --> 00:09:43,390
I'm craving ice cream.

133
00:09:43,390 --> 00:09:45,550
Let's get some.

134
00:09:46,310 --> 00:09:49,000
<i>I can tell you wouldn't do that,</i>

135
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:52,110
<i>even though we haven't
known each other for long.</i>

136
00:09:52,110 --> 00:09:54,100
<i>I'm on your side.</i>

137
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,580
<i>It's okay.</i>

138
00:09:57,580 --> 00:10:01,110
<i>I have someone who really understands me.</i>

139
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,340
Good work today.

140
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:10,490
Oh! Ama. Good work today.

141
00:10:10,490 --> 00:10:13,620
Mr. Hachimura, thanks.

142
00:10:13,620 --> 00:10:17,450
Oh, this scene...
I'm a bit nervous about it too.

143
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:19,580
Wanna read together?

144
00:10:19,580 --> 00:10:21,630
- Yes, please.
- Right?

145
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:26,835
- This is the scene, right?
- Yeah.

146
00:10:26,835 --> 00:10:28,447
Okay, let's start from

147
00:10:28,447 --> 00:10:30,500
- the stage directions here.
- Okay.

148
00:10:35,390 --> 00:10:37,260
Thank you so much.

149
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:39,370
- No, no, thank you.
- You helped so much.

150
00:10:39,370 --> 00:10:42,180
But you know, with today's scene,

151
00:10:42,180 --> 00:10:43,960
I'm glad we talked it through.

152
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:46,450
I had fun, thanks to you.

153
00:10:46,450 --> 00:10:47,590
- Really?
- Yes.

154
00:10:47,590 --> 00:10:50,450
- Then I'm glad.
- Good work, Ama.

155
00:10:51,330 --> 00:10:53,180
Chiaki.

156
00:10:53,770 --> 00:10:55,800
Oh, Mr. Hosho,
thanks for your hard work.

157
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,210
Good work.

158
00:10:57,210 --> 00:10:58,870
Well, Ama, see you later.

159
00:10:58,870 --> 00:11:01,463
- Yes, I'll see you next time.
- Thank you.

160
00:11:01,463 --> 00:11:03,650
- See you.
- Good work!

161
00:11:11,330 --> 00:11:13,450
Are you two close?

162
00:11:14,170 --> 00:11:18,480
Mr. Hachimura and I share a lot of scenes,
so he's been very kind.

163
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:21,980
I see.

164
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:27,360
Is something wrong?

165
00:11:34,264 --> 00:11:36,814
I was just thinking...

166
00:11:37,836 --> 00:11:40,480
that I want to be the closest to you.

167
00:11:41,865 --> 00:11:43,305
Huh?

168
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:46,040
I'll take you home.

169
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,590
I drove here today.

170
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,400
<i>No matter how close you get to him,</i>

171
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:55,020
<i>don't make any mistakes with Mr. Hosho,
alright?</i>

172
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:59,170
<i>How could I ever, with a star like that?</i>

173
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:02,974
But I don't want to impose.

174
00:12:05,490 --> 00:12:07,720
I want to.

175
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:11,310
We haven't talked much today.

176
00:12:14,410 --> 00:12:18,710
Well, if you insist.

177
00:12:18,710 --> 00:12:20,170
Okay.

178
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:26,870
Oh, you're good at cooking?

179
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:31,200
I wouldn't say good,
but budget cooking is kind of my hobby.

180
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,730
I want to try it.

181
00:12:32,730 --> 00:12:35,550
Your budget cooking.

182
00:12:35,550 --> 00:12:38,620
Oh, it's nothing I could serve to someone.

183
00:12:38,620 --> 00:12:40,170
It doesn't matter.

184
00:12:40,170 --> 00:12:43,420
I'm fine with anything you cook, Ama.

185
00:12:43,420 --> 00:12:47,020
If you'd like, why don't you stay for dinner?

186
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:50,420
Are you sure?

187
00:12:50,420 --> 00:12:51,540
Of course!

188
00:12:51,540 --> 00:12:54,160
You've been so helpful to me.

189
00:12:57,760 --> 00:13:02,570
But... Chiaki, you might be surprised
when you see my place.

190
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:05,420
Surprised?

191
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:17,610
This really isn't a place
people would invite you to, huh?

192
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:21,560
Oh, no, that's not true at all.

193
00:13:23,930 --> 00:13:25,740
He's so cool!

194
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:27,840
Let's pretend to transform!

195
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:31,860
Transform! Transform!
Transform! Transform!

196
00:13:31,860 --> 00:13:34,690
Hey, don't bother Chiaki!

197
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:38,670
No, it's okay. Don't mind me.

198
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:40,160
Sorry.

199
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:46,696
Transform, transform,
transform, transform...

200
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:50,290
Belt, fwoosh!

201
00:13:50,290 --> 00:13:52,470
Belt, fwoosh!

202
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:54,300
Fwoosh!

203
00:13:55,530 --> 00:13:58,660
Your senior is a nice person.

204
00:13:58,660 --> 00:14:00,060
Yeah.

205
00:14:00,990 --> 00:14:05,840
Special Kicky! Kicky!

206
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:08,470
He's a really good person.

207
00:14:08,470 --> 00:14:12,310
I beat you! Yay!

208
00:14:14,110 --> 00:14:16,910
Thanks for the meal.

209
00:14:16,910 --> 00:14:21,680
A Minase family special,
curry that's more like a soup.

210
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,270
Wait, I'm sorry.

211
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:26,210
This is way too ordinary, isn't it?

212
00:14:26,210 --> 00:14:28,600
Sis's curry is really good!

213
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,661
I always ask for seconds!

214
00:14:30,661 --> 00:14:32,730
- Right?
- That's true.

215
00:14:32,730 --> 00:14:34,850
Really?

216
00:14:34,850 --> 00:14:37,090
Thanks for the meal.

217
00:14:45,092 --> 00:14:46,702
It's good.

218
00:14:48,540 --> 00:14:50,400
I'm glad to hear that.

219
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:54,970
Sei, it's all over your mouth.

220
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:57,210
Sei, look this way.

221
00:14:57,210 --> 00:15:00,720
There, let's clean that face up.

222
00:15:01,401 --> 00:15:05,011
- So gross!
- Hey!

223
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:10,900
You always have curry
all over your face too, Nagi!

224
00:15:19,110 --> 00:15:21,510
Is something wrong?

225
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:24,620
No.

226
00:15:25,270 --> 00:15:29,080
It's been so long since I had home cooking.

227
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:32,650
Hey, sis is also good at "Jaga"!

228
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,640
"Jaga"?

229
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:38,010
That's what we call
our meat and potato stew.

230
00:15:38,010 --> 00:15:40,340
But there's no meat in it.

231
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:44,990
Oh, so that's why it's "Jaga".
(*Jaga means "potato")

232
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:51,370
I'd like to try that "Jaga" sometime.

233
00:15:52,330 --> 00:15:55,040
Yes, of course.

234
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:59,180
Yay! We get to eat Sis's "Jaga" next time!

235
00:15:59,180 --> 00:16:02,630
Yay! I want to eat it soon! Yay!

236
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:08,549
Thank you for the meal.

237
00:16:08,549 --> 00:16:10,410
It was delicious.

238
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:13,330
I'm so glad you liked it.

239
00:16:13,330 --> 00:16:15,650
No, really.

240
00:16:19,190 --> 00:16:24,140
I think I get why
you're the way you are now, Ama.

241
00:16:25,810 --> 00:16:30,050
That's definitely not a compliment, is it?

242
00:16:30,050 --> 00:16:31,900
No.

243
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:35,670
For me, it's the highest compliment.

244
00:16:36,810 --> 00:16:39,000
Is it?

245
00:16:39,590 --> 00:16:41,010
Yeah.

246
00:16:54,570 --> 00:16:55,870
Hello?

247
00:16:55,870 --> 00:16:57,520
So?

248
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:59,690
Did you get that girl?

249
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,670
Don't rush me.

250
00:17:02,670 --> 00:17:04,380
We still have time, right?

251
00:17:04,380 --> 00:17:08,410
Don't tell me you're actually struggling?

252
00:17:10,170 --> 00:17:11,910
Shut up.

253
00:17:27,740 --> 00:17:30,540
Today's a long day.

254
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:32,820
Good morning.

255
00:17:32,820 --> 00:17:35,150
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

256
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:41,160
Good morning.

257
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:43,380
Thanks for yesterday.

258
00:17:43,380 --> 00:17:47,320
No, thank you.

259
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:49,480
Huh, what's this, what's this?

260
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,940
Hey, are you two getting close?

261
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:54,580
No, no, that's not it, not at all.

262
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:58,970
How could someone like me
ever have a thing with Chiaki?

263
00:17:58,970 --> 00:18:01,180
No way!

264
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:04,150
Oh, then, Ama.

265
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:05,230
How about me?

266
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:07,697
I mean, in this movie, we're playing lovers.

267
00:18:07,697 --> 00:18:10,510
Jeez, don't tease me, Mr. Hachimura.

268
00:18:10,510 --> 00:18:12,650
No, I'm not teasing you.

269
00:18:12,650 --> 00:18:14,790
Hey, don't laugh!

270
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,560
No.

271
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,840
Ama is mine.

272
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:27,690
Huh?

273
00:18:34,950 --> 00:18:38,420
Chiaki, please don't tease me either!

274
00:18:49,810 --> 00:18:54,890
<i>I feel like Chiaki and I have gotten closer.</i>

275
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:01,920
<i>What am I thinking?</i>

276
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,150
Thanks for your hard work.

277
00:19:03,150 --> 00:19:05,260
I'll see you again tomorrow.

278
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:07,320
Good work today.

279
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:18,210
You're ignoring my calls. The nerve.

280
00:19:22,180 --> 00:19:24,290
Chiaki?

281
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:27,540
I've told you repeatedly.

282
00:19:27,540 --> 00:19:29,050
Don't come to my workplace.

283
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:32,430
Whatever. Just hand over the cash.

284
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,680
Come on, hurry up!

285
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:40,560
<i>I need to get someone.</i>

286
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:44,060
Can't you even listen to your mother?

287
00:19:44,060 --> 00:19:45,990
<i>Huh?</i>

288
00:19:45,990 --> 00:19:49,760
<i>Chiaki's mom?</i>

289
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:53,110
What's with that look?

290
00:19:54,740 --> 00:19:58,080
You're looking more and more like that man.

291
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:02,200
You make me so mad.

292
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:06,000
I wish I'd never given birth to you.

293
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:08,350
You useless thing!

294
00:20:32,150 --> 00:20:34,240
What? Who are you?

295
00:20:35,460 --> 00:20:37,710
What do you think you're doing?

296
00:20:39,230 --> 00:20:40,970
None of your business. Move over.

297
00:20:40,970 --> 00:20:44,750
I can't just stand by while you hurt Chiaki.

298
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:54,610
I see, I see.

299
00:20:54,610 --> 00:20:57,430
You're being fooled, you know?

300
00:20:57,430 --> 00:21:00,880
This guy isn't worth protecting.

301
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:03,440
He's a worthless guy with a pretty face.

302
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:07,930
You're his mother. How could you say that?

303
00:21:08,610 --> 00:21:11,530
Chiaki is not worthless!

304
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:19,310
He's kind, and caring.

305
00:21:19,310 --> 00:21:22,780
He saw something in someone like me.

306
00:21:24,970 --> 00:21:28,170
He's a very important person to me!

307
00:21:32,450 --> 00:21:34,160
You hear that?

308
00:21:34,820 --> 00:21:38,600
You're still a good actor, aren't you?

309
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:43,590
By the way,
I recorded our conversation just now.

310
00:21:43,590 --> 00:21:45,010
What?

311
00:21:47,190 --> 00:21:49,760
- Give me that!
- It's no use.

312
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:52,570
I already sent it to another device.

313
00:21:56,010 --> 00:21:59,530
Don't ever do anything like this
to Chiaki again.

314
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:16,560
<i>Thank goodness.</i>

315
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:19,590
<i>The recording was a lie I made up just now.</i>

316
00:22:20,780 --> 00:22:23,560
Chiaki, are you okay?

317
00:22:37,130 --> 00:22:38,650
Chiaki?

318
00:22:38,650 --> 00:22:40,700
Are you okay?

319
00:22:43,250 --> 00:22:45,250
I'll go get someone.

320
00:22:51,330 --> 00:22:53,000
Please.

321
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:59,080
Don't move.

322
00:23:01,550 --> 00:23:03,480
Stay with me.

323
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:23,240
Whenever I hear her voice, I can't move.

324
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:25,950
It's all because of you
that my life is a mess!

325
00:23:25,950 --> 00:23:27,010
It's pathetic.

326
00:23:27,010 --> 00:23:29,130
There's nothing pathetic about that.

327
00:23:29,130 --> 00:23:31,590
I'll protect you, Chiaki.

328
00:23:31,590 --> 00:23:33,370
Disappear, disappear, disappear!

329
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:36,500
You're such an eyesore!

330
00:23:37,770 --> 00:23:39,580
Ama.

331
00:23:39,580 --> 00:23:42,330
I've always wanted to apologize to you, Ama.

332
00:23:42,330 --> 00:23:45,170
You're cuter than anyone, Ama.

333
00:23:45,170 --> 00:23:46,620
But it's okay.

334
00:23:46,620 --> 00:23:49,480
I'll stay by your side, Ama.

